      "@wereHamster can you post the output of `r.table(...).config()` and `r.table(...).status()`?\r\n\r\nCould you also email me the output of `r.db('rethinkdb').table('_debug_table_status')` (daniel@rethinkdb.com)?\r\n\r\nAfter you're retrieved the output of these commands, these steps might help recover from the situation:\r\n1. Shut down the secondary\r\n2. On the primary, run `r.table(...).reconfigure({emergency_repair: 'unsafe_rollback'})`\r\n3. Restart the secondary\r\n4. Run `r.table(...).reconfigure({replicas: 2, shards: 1})` to restore the original configuration\r\n\r\nNote that this process can in some cases lose the last few seconds worth of writes, if they hadn't been fully written to both replicas yet."
